# Installation

Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/dweepvira/water-treatment_simulator_CPS.git
cd water-treatment_simulator_CPS
```

Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

# Running the Simulator

## Step 1 — Start PLC Simulation

Load the Structured Text program in **CODESYS**

```
ST_code/plant.st
```

Run the PLC runtime and ensure the **Modbus TCP server is active**.

---

## Step 2 — Run Dataset Generator

Start the automated dataset generator.

```bash
python automated_dataset_generator.py --host <PLC_IP>
```

Example

```bash
python automated_dataset_generator.py --host 192.168.0.163
```

This script logs:

- process variables
- attack labels
- system states
- timestamps

---

# Attack Simulation

The system includes multiple cyber-attack scenarios that target PLC operations.

---

# Command Injection Attack

Manipulates PLC control commands such as pumps or valves.

```bash
python attacks/command_injection.py --host <PLC_IP>
```

Example

```bash
python attacks/command_injection.py --host 192.168.0.163
```

Effects:

- Forces pumps ON/OFF
- Opens or closes valves
- Alters system behavior

---

# Denial of Service (DoS)

Floods PLC communication using Modbus requests.

```bash
python attacks/dos_replay.py --host <PLC_IP>
```

Effects:

- Communication delays
- Control loop disruption
- System instability

---

# Reconnaissance Attack

Scans Modbus registers to discover PLC variables.

```bash
python attacks/reconnaissance.py --host <PLC_IP>
```

Effects:

- Maps PLC memory
- Identifies sensors and actuators
- Enables targeted attacks

---

# Dataset Generation

Each execution generates a run folder.

Example:

```
run_01
run_02
run_03
run_04
run_05
```

Each run contains:

```
master_dataset.csv
attack_metadata.json
attack_timeline.log
execution_details.log
```

These datasets combine:

- normal process behaviour
- attack periods
- sensor values
- control signals

---

# Feature Engineering

Generate ML features.

```bash
python feature_engineering.py
```

Extracted features include

```
sensor deltas
temporal gradients
rolling averages
rate of change
statistical features
```

Outputs:

```
features.csv
labels.csv
X_scaled.npy
```

---

# Machine Learning Training

Train anomaly detection models.

```bash
python ml_training.py
```

Supported models

```
LightGBM
Random Forest
Gradient Boosting
```

Outputs

```
trained_models/
feature_importance.png
confusion_matrix.png
model_metadata.json
```

---

# Real-Time Intrusion Detection

Run the detection system.

```bash
python real_time_detect.py
```

Pipeline

```
Live PLC Data
      ↓
Feature Extraction
      ↓
Trained Model
      ↓
Attack Prediction
```

